        <h2 class="title"><a href="/archives/000082.html">Term for people blabbering on cell phones</a></h2>    <span class="submitted">Submitted by <a href="/user/brad" title="View user profile." rel="nofollow">brad</a> on Sat, 2004-05-08 15:23.</span>
    <span class="taxonomy"><ul class="links inline"><li class="first taxonomy_term_19"><a href="/archives/cat_best_of_blog.html" rel="tag" title="Blog postings that have been most popular, or which have said things I really wanted to say." class="taxonomy_term_19">Best Of Blog</a></li>
<li class="last taxonomy_term_14"><a href="/archives/cat_random_ideas.html" rel="tag" title="" class="taxonomy_term_14">Random Ideas</a></li>
</ul></span>
    <div class="content"><p>You have all seen them standing on sidewalks, talking loudly to nobody, waving their arms.  Too well dressed to be crazy homeless folks -- then you notice the earbud, and know they are on a cell phone.   We need a term for these people and this phenomenon.</p>
<p>Some ideas:</p>
<ul>
<li>Cellchotic (and Cellchosis)</p>
<li>Schizophonia  (And the afflicted are Schizophonics)
<li>Celliloquists (not as derogatory)
</ul>
<p>Your ideas?</p>
</div>
