        <h2 class="title"><a href="/archives/000069.html">Some new terms to throw out</a></h2>    <span class="submitted">Submitted by <a href="/user/brad" title="View user profile." rel="nofollow">brad</a> on Mon, 2004-04-19 06:09.</span>
    <span class="taxonomy"><ul class="links inline"><li class="first taxonomy_term_2"><a href="/archives/cat_comedy.html" rel="tag" title="" class="taxonomy_term_2">Comedy</a></li>
<li class="last taxonomy_term_14"><a href="/archives/cat_random_ideas.html" rel="tag" title="" class="taxonomy_term_14">Random Ideas</a></li>
</ul></span>
    <div class="content"><p>I like to make up terms.  Here are some more for your use or enjoyment.</p>
<dl>
<dt>Re-fried<br />
<dd>Returned to Fry's Electronics and re-shrinkwrapped.  "Don't buy that one, it's been re-fried!"</p>
<dt>Nerd Trolling<br />
<dd>For women who want a geeky guy, dressing up to the 9s and going out on Friday night to the computer store, then standing in front of the hard drives muttering about whether you should get SATA, IDE or SCSI.  The guys there alone Friday night are single, smart and probably well off or gainfully employed.  Much better odds than the bars.</p>
<dt>Post-Futurism<br />
<dd>Modern, post-modern and futurist are not enough.  If you're into the Singularity, worry about Gray Goo and copying uploaded human minds, you're a post-futurist.<br />
</dl>
